:3:"wfw";s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";s:2:"dc";s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";s:4:"atom";s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";s:2:"sy";s:44:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/";s:5:"slash";s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";s:10:"feedburner";s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";s:5:"xhtml";s:28:"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml";s:6:"atom10";s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";}}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:2442:"<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="post_img aligncenter size-full wp-image-1334" src="http://newinternetorder.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/pb4.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="272" /></p>\n<p>The fact that I’m using images a lot on this blog is not accidental. It’s also not because I have some particular feelings towards photography and its different forms. Well okay, I do like to take a nice picture every now and then, but that’s not the point here.</p>\n<p>The main reason why I’m using images along with my posts is because they add additional impact to them, making the posts more memorable and distinctive.</p>\n<p>I’m sorry to use the cliché, but a picture is really worth a thousand words. Especially if it’s presented next to a post of 1000 words or more…<span id="more-1332"></span></p>\n<p>A couple of weeks ago we were discussing various places where you can get <a href="http://newinternetorder.com/where-to-get-the-images-for-your-blog/">images for your blog</a>. Today it’s time to answer the “<em>how</em>” part of the issue. So check out <strong>my guest post at ProBlogger </strong>to find out what I’m on about:</p>\n<p align="center"><a href="http://newinternetorder.com/images-in-your-blog-posts" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">How to Use Images in Your Blog Posts</a></p>\n<p>And I know, okay, I didn’t use any images in that particular post. But I do it a lot in my other posts so please bear with me <img src=''http://newinternetorder.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>Also, what do you think about the whole idea of using images as an important part of every blog post?</p>\n<b>Related Posts</b>:\n<ul>\n		<li><a href="http://newinternetorder.com/where-to-get-the-images-for-your-blog/">Where to Get the Images for Your Blog</a><!-- (7.1)--></li>\n		<li><a href="http://newinternetorder.com/being-drunk-vs-marketing-and-life/">What Being Drunk Can Teach You About Marketing and Life</a><!-- (4.8)--></li>\n		<li><a href="http://newinternetorder.com/12-quotations-on-success/">12 Quotations on Success That Are Sure to Change Your Life</a><!-- (4.8)--></li>\n	</ul>\n<p><br /><a href="http://newinternetorder.com/images-in-blog-posts/">Add a Little Life to Your Content &#8211; Use Images</a> | <a href="http://newinternetorder.com">newInternetOrder.com</a></p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/nio/~4/-rwMsQWHqiE" height="1" width="1"/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"xmlns";a:9:{s:7:"content";s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";s:3:"wfw";s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";s:2:"dc";s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";s:4:"atom";s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";s:2:"sy";s:44:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/";s:5:"slash";s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";s:10:"feedburner";s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";s:5:"xhtml";s:28:"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml";s:6:"atom10";s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";}}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:54:"http://newinternetorder.com/images-in-blog-posts/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"xmlns";a:9:{s:7:"content";s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";s:3:"wfw";s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";s:2:"dc";s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elem