d it useful. Not a perfect little snippet, but gets the job done. Note the use of the little-used 307 redirect for temporary redirection. This is to make [...]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"xmlns";a:7:{s:7:"content";s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";s:3:"wfw";s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";s:2:"dc";s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";s:4:"atom";s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";s:2:"sy";s:44:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/";s:5:"slash";s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";s:5:"media";s:29:"http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/";}}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:4:"Otto";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"xmlns";a:7:{s:7:"content";s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";s:3:"wfw";s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";s:2:"dc";s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";s:4:"atom";s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";s:2:"sy";s:44:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/";s:5:"slash";s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";s:5:"media";s:29:"http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/";}}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:2301:"<fb:like href=''http://ottopress.com/2011/random-post-snippet/'' send=''true'' layout=''standard'' show_faces=''true'' width=''450'' height=''65'' action=''recommend'' colorscheme=''light'' font=''lucida+grande''></fb:like><p><img class="alignright size-full wp-image-702" title="phpcode" src="http://ottopress.com/files/2011/10/phpcode.png" alt="" width="200" height="100" /><br />\nWrote this quick WordPress code snippet at WordCamp Louisville. It makes a /random/ URL on your site which redirects to a random post. Thought some people might find it useful.</p>\n<p>Not a perfect little snippet, but gets the job done. Note the use of the little-used 307 redirect for temporary redirection. This is to make browsers not cache the results of the redirect, like some of them might do with a 302.</p>\n<pre class="brush: php; notranslate">\nadd_action(''init'',''random_add_rewrite'');\nfunction random_add_rewrite() {\n       global $wp;\n       $wp-&gt;add_query_var(''random'');\n       add_rewrite_rule(''random/?$'', ''index.php?random=1'', ''top'');\n}\n\nadd_action(''template_redirect'',''random_template'');\nfunction random_template() {\n       if (get_query_var(''random'') == 1) {\n               $posts = get_posts(''post_type=post&amp;orderby=rand&amp;numberposts=1'');\n               foreach($posts as $post) {\n                       $link = get_permalink($post);\n               }\n               wp_redirect($link,307);\n               exit;\n       }\n}\n</pre>\n<p>There&#8217;s plugins that do this sort of thing too, but this is such a simple little thing that it doesn&#8217;t really need a big amount of code to do.</p>\n<p><em>Edit</em>: Added get_permalink() optimization from @Raherian.</p>\n<a href=''http://twitter.com/share?url=http%3A%2F%2Fotto42.com%2Fax&count=vertical&related=otto42%2Cottodestruct&text=Random Post snippet'' class=''twitter-share-button'' data-text=''Random Post snippet'' data-url=''http://otto42.com/ax'' data-counturl=''http://ottopress.com/2011/random-post-snippet/'' data-count=''vertical'' data-via=''ottodestruct'' data-related=''otto42,ottodestruct''></a><span class="fb_share"><fb:like href="http://ottopress.com/2011/random-post-snippet/" layout="box_count"></fb:like></span><div class="plusone"><g:plusone size=tall annotation=bubble align=left href="http://ottopress.com/2011/random-post-snippet/"></g:plusone></div>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"xmlns";a:7:{s:7:"content";s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";s:3:"wfw";s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";s:2:"dc";s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";s