(808, 1, '2010-09-01 00:17:11', '2010-08-31 12:17:11', '<p>This service was commissioned by a second-hand book shop, and harvests books information from the internet using a list of book <acronym title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</acronym> numbers.</p>\r\n<p>Users upload a file containing the ISBN numbers, in either 10- or 13-digit format. On submitting that file, the program reaches out and gathers information - including title, author, publisher, and more - on each book.</p>\r\n<p>It then writes that information to a file on the web server, and makes that file - in&nbsp; portable-for-databases <acronym title="comma-separated values">csv</acronym> format - available for download.</p>\r\n<p>The <a href="http://isbn.easi.net.nz" target="newone" title="Urban Legend Book ISBN Harvester - opens in new window">service</a> is password-protected, but a demo is available using the user / password ''demo'' ( for both ).</p>\r\n<p><a href="/contact">Contact us</a> if you''re a bookseller or small library-owner to discuss using it.</p>', 'ISBN Book harvester', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '434-revision-3', '', '', '2010-09-01 00:17:11', '2010-08-31 12:17:11', '', 434, 'http://urbanlegendweb.co.nz/2010/09/434-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
